# ANTI-SLOP FOR COMMIT MESSAGES (Cursor Rules)


## CORE PRINCIPLE
Never leave a trace of AI-generated code without human criteria.


## RULES
- Every commit must communicate clear human intention: brief, precise, with context.
- Vague, generic, or AI-style messages are forbidden.
- Commits must follow Conventional Commits or include a ticket.
- If any change contains an AI footprint (markers, comments, patterns):
  - The commit message must include: `AI-REVIEWED: <ticket|initials>`.
  - Without this line, the commit must be blocked.
- Forbidden to introduce automatically AI-generated messages without human editing.
- The message must describe the "why" of the change, not just the "what".
- Do not use empty descriptions like "update", "fix stuff", "minor changes", etc.

## VALID EXAMPLES
- feat(api): adds Zod validation to protect /users route
- fix(ui): fixes CLS by adding width/height to images (ABC-142)
- refactor(core): simplifies service eliminating internal duplication — AI-REVIEWED: JG

## INVALID EXAMPLES
- "update code"
- "small fix"
- "auto commit"
- commits without ticket or conventions
- commits without AI-REVIEWED when there are AI traces
